  "prompt": "Can you check your WhatsApp from another phone?",
  "response": "Yes, you can access your WhatsApp account from another phone, but there are specific limitations and steps involved. Here are the main methods to do so:\n\n1. **WhatsApp Web/Desktop:**\n   - If you want to access your WhatsApp from another device temporarily, you can use WhatsApp Web or the WhatsApp Desktop application. This method requires that your primary phone is connected to the internet.\n   - To do this, open WhatsApp on your primary phone, go to **Settings** > **Linked Devices**, and then use your phone to scan the QR code shown on the WhatsApp Web or Desktop application on the other device.\n\n2. **Switching Devices:**\n   - If you want to actively use WhatsApp on a different phone, you need to install WhatsApp on the new device and register your phone number. This process will deactivate WhatsApp on the other phone since WhatsApp only allows one active instance with the same phone number on mobile devices.\n   - You will receive a verification code on your number, which you need to enter on the new device to activate it.\n\nAlways remember to back up your chat history before switching devices if you want to retain your chat history. Use the backup feature in WhatsApp settings to upload your data to Google Drive or iCloud, depending on your device's operating system.",
